<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1630">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.819.74/4.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs has told me in conversation that his
                            Government will enter into such an understanding as that indicated in
                            your telegram of December 16, if necessary for protecting the canal and
                            the interests of the United States, but hopes such an understanding will
                            not prevent such use of wireless telegraphy as might aid the development
                            of Panama.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>